/a></figure></div><div class=\"wpb_single_image wpb_content_element vc_align_left\" style=\"margin-bottom: 35px; text-align: left;\"><figure class=\"wpb_wrapper vc_figure\" style=\"display: inline-block; vertical-align: top; max-width: 100%;\"><a href=\"https://www.georgebrown.ca/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"vc_single_image-wrapper vc_box_border  vc_box_border_grey\" style=\"background-color: rgb(235, 235, 235); color: rgb(44, 117, 228); outline: 0px; transition: 0.25s; border: none; display: inline-block; vertical-align: top; max-width: 100%; border-radius: 0px; box-shadow: none; padding: 6px; text-decoration: none !important;\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"vc_single_image-img attachment-thumbnail entered lazyloaded\" alt=\"\" title=\"Geroge_Brown_College\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?w=200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?resize=129%2C129&amp;ssl=1 129w, https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?resize=69%2C69&amp;ssl=1 69w, https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?resize=20%2C20&amp;ssl=1 20w, https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?resize=100%2C100&amp;ssl=1 100w\" data-lazy-sizes=\"(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" data-lazy-src=\"https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1\" data-ll-status=\"loaded\" sizes=\"(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?w=200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?resize=129%2C129&amp;ssl=1 129w, https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?resize=69%2C69&amp;ssl=1 69w, https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?resize=20%2C20&amp;ssl=1 20w, https://i0.wp.com/pecpte.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Geroge_Brown_College.png?resize=100%2C100&amp;ssl=1 100w\" style=\"border: none; vertical-align: top; max-width: 100%; height: auto; border-radius: 0px; box-shadow: none;\"></a></figure></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-6\" style=\"width: 600px; position: relative; min-height: 1px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; float: left; color: rgb(39, 48, 68); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\"><div class=\"vc_column-inner\" style=\"padding-left: 15px; padding-right: 15px; width: 600px;\"><div class=\"wpb_wrapper\"><div class=\"wpb_text_column wpb_content_element \" style=\"margin-bottom: 35px;\"><div class=\"wpb_wrapper\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px;\"><h1 style=\"font-size: 50px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 0px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 55px; color: rgb(39, 48, 68); text-align: left; letter-spacing: -0.4px;\">Study in Canada from Bangladesh</h1><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 0px;\">Canada is developed country where high quality of education is guaranteed. Moreover, Canadian Universities now provide ample educational opportunities to Bangladeshi Students. Canadian Universities are well known for their affordable tuition fee. Moreover, Canadian degree is globally recognized as being equivalent to that obtained from the United States or Commonwealth countries. Another more attraction for international students is the possibility of immigration. There is no on/off campus part time job restrictions in Canada which is helpful to save your wallet.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 0px;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0px;\">Canadian Provinces and Universities to Consider:</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 0px;\">Canada has a well- recognized position among the world’s leading study destinations. The most popular Canadian provinces for international students are Ontario, British Columbia and Quebec, Regina,&nbsp;<em style=\"margin-bottom: 0px;\">Saskatchewan</em>&nbsp;which between them are abode to many of the top&nbsp;universities in Canada.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 0px;\">For those looking to study at a famous university in one of the world’s most developed nations, applying to study in Canada can be an exact option.&nbsp;A total of 26 universities in Canada feature in the&nbsp;QS World University Ranking, of which three are in the world’s top 50, with 11 more making the world’s top 300 – a feat matched only by a handful of other nations.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 0px;\">The two highest Canadian entries are the University of Waterloo and University of Windsor, located in Toronto, largest city in Canada. Also ranked within the global top 220 are the Brock University, Lakehead University, University of manitoba, Trent University, Thompson Rivers university, University of Regina, University of Saskatchewan and Western University etc .</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 0px;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0px;\">Canadian Education System</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 0px;\">Undergraduate degrees in Canada can take either three or four years to complete, depending on the university. Postgraduate degrees take between one and three years to complete, depending on the type of degree. Different types of higher education providers in Canada include: universities (which carry out research and provide both undergraduate and postgraduate degrees), community colleges and technical, applied arts or applied science schools (which grant certificates, diplomas,&nbsp;&nbsp;and bachelor’s degrees).</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 0px;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0px;\">Reasons to Study in Canada</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 0px;\">95% of international students recommend Canada as a study destination! Different reasons claim that Canada is the best option like</p><ol style=\"margin-bottom: 25px; padding-left: 20px;\"><li style=\"margin-bottom: 8px;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0px;\">Multi Culture.</strong>&nbsp;International Student will be able to communicate and cooperate with 300 nationalities from all over the world in Canada</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 8px;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0px;\">Affordable Tuition fee and living cost</strong>. Canadian Education and Life is rather affordable in comparison with other English speaking countries. Also, student will be able to work legally during their education in Canada.</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 8px;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0px;\">Beautiful Nature</strong>. Canada is full of picturesque places and sightseeing’s, which everybody have to visit.</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 0px;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0px;\">No racism among People.&nbsp;</strong>Most Canadians ready to help and assist newcomers with any questions, which can arise after coming to Canada.</li></ol><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 0px;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0px;\">Facilities to study in Canada:</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 0px;\">Students from different parts of the world move to Canada for its educational facilities. Canadian schools are ranked among the top in the world with research industries trailblazing the fields of business, engineering, healthcare, technology and more! Beyond the quality of the education, Canada is a basis of multiculturalism with Canadian learning institutions not merely tolerating cultural diversity, but celebrating it! Any student experience in Canada, international or not, is sure to offer rich insight and appreciation for other cultures.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 0px;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: bold;\">&nbsp;</strong><strong style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0px;\">English Language Proficiency Test:</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-left: 0px;\">Universities advise all applicants what standard of English is required for their courses. Most course providers will ask you to demonstrate proficiency in English, or to take an approved English language test if English is not your first language. Required PTE-Academic Score for the under graduation in Canada is 55 and IELTS Score is 6, for post graduation is 59 in PTE Academic and IELTS score is 6.5. Please contact us for the proper training of PTE/ IELTS for your better score.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Opportunity after Study</strong><br style=\"margin-bottom: 0px;\">Studying in Canada also paves the way for international students to achieve permanent Canadian immigration! After completing studies in Canada, foreign nationals can become eligible for a number of&nbsp;immigration pathways, including post-graduation work permits, provincial nominee programs, even fast-tracked permanent resident status. Anyone serious about immigration in Canada should consider whether becoming a Canadian international student could be the best first step!</p></div></div></div></div></div>', '2026-03-23 10:44:28');
